###
# End-to-end flow (Location + Ride + Kafka side effects)
# This file focuses on HTTP requests. Kafka verification is done via logs/topic consumer.

### Step 1) Seed a nearby driver
POST {{locationBaseUrl}}/api/v1/locations/drivers/update-location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "driveId": "driver-e2e-1",
  "latitude": 24.7136,
  "longitude": 46.6753
}

### Step 2) Check nearby driver exists
GET {{locationBaseUrl}}/api/v1/locations/drivers/nearby?latitude=24.7136&longitude=46.6753&radiusKm=5
Accept: application/json

### Step 3) Create ride request (publishes ride.requested)
POST {{rideBaseUrl}}/api/rides/request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "riderId": "rider-e2e-1",
  "pickupLatitude": 24.7136,
  "pickupLongitude": 46.6753,
  "pickupAddress": "E2E Pickup",
  "dropLatitude": 24.774265,
  "dropLongitude": 46.738586,
  "dropAddress": "E2E Drop"
}

# Expected runtime side effects:
# - wasel-ride log: Published RideRequestEvent for rideId: <id>
# - wasel-matchin log: Received ride event: ...
# - wasel-matchin log: Ride matched and event published: ...
# - Kafka topic ride.requested gets one message
# - Kafka topic ride.matched gets one message

### Step 4) Fetch rider rides
GET {{rideBaseUrl}}/api/rides/rider/rider-e2e-1
Accept: application/json

### Step 5) Cleanup test driver location
DELETE {{locationBaseUrl}}/api/v1/locations/drivers/driver-e2e-1?driverId=driver-e2e-1

